data.description:
Former Bent Creek Model Home, Extra bonus rm or 4th bedroom, Large eat-in kitchen w/ lots of cabinet space and counter seating, Large bedrooms, Master w/ double vanity, walk-in closet and garden tub, Hardwood floors/Carpeting, Huge level yard, Covered front porch w/ swing, Rear deck, Vaulted ceilings, Cul-de-sac, Plenty of inside storage space, Oversized garage, Dual H/A (separate units and thermostats for upstairs and downstairs), New downstairs unit installed Dec. '06, New siding installed in Dec. '06, New upgraded roof installed in Sept. '09, new carpet installed throughout in July '16, new flooring in upstairs baths in 2018, Alarm system, Back yard fenced in on two of three sides with nice wood picket fencing...courtesy of our very kind neighbors. All wallpaper has been stripped and walls painted with soothing neutral colors. Overall, this home is impeccably maintained.


Neighborhood Description


Located within the Bent Creek Subdivision in the Karns community, this area is surburban living in the midst of the country.  Karns is a quiet community located just minutes away form the hustle and bustle of West Knoxville with all of it's big city ammenities.  This home is  situated on a quiet and very secure culdesac in a small subdivision which is adjacent to the Butler Farm and other wide open spaces.   The country setting is peaceful and serene, and the everyday stress of life seems to fade as one approaches home after a hard day's work.  There's no place like this home!
data.whatILove: Wide roads and large lots with mature landscaping make this subdivision a rare find when compared to the newer tight lot subdivisions with narrow roads and a lack of trees and other landscaping.  This home has large bedrooms, kitchen area and rear deck which have all combined to make it a great home for entertaining large groups of our friends.
